<h4>
    Resistors of less than 10 Ohms
</h4>

<p>
    A resistor can have a resistance of less than 10 Ohms if the third band is either silver or gold.
    If gold, the third number is -1, and if silver, the third number is -2.
    Both correspond to moving the decimal point to the left.
</p>
<p class = 'equation'>
    $$
    [\text{First Number}] [\text{Second Number}] \cdot 10^{[\text{Third Number}]}
    $$
</p>

